# {{.ProjectName}}

Codex executable runtime scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This lane is for repo-local Codex notify integration in `{{.Runtime}}`, not for the official Codex plugin bundle.
It is a stable supported path for Python and Node teams, not a second-class fallback.
{{- if .IsCustomLogicTemplate }}

This is the advanced custom-logic path. Choose it when the plugin's value lives in your runtime code, hooks, or orchestration logic instead of only wiring an existing service or local tool.

## What You Edit First

- `plugin/plugin.yaml`: shared plugin identity and target scope
- `plugin/launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint metadata
- `plugin/main.{{if eq .Runtime "python"}}py{{else if eq .Runtime "node"}}{{if .TypeScript}}ts{{else}}mjs{{end}}{{else}}sh{{end}}` or `scripts/main.sh`: the runtime entrypoint you own
- `plugin/targets/codex-runtime/...`: authored Codex runtime metadata

## What Gets Generated

- managed guidance files at the repo root such as `README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `GENERATED.md`
- native Codex output such as `.codex/config.toml`

Start with this `plugin/README.md`, then run `plugin-kit-ai inspect . --authoring` before you expand the repo into more outputs.
{{- end }}

