## Bootstrap Contract

{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
- Runtime requirement: Python `3.10+` installed on the machine running the plugin
- Preferred runtime: project `.venv`
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- Shared helper delivery: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on PyPI
- Generated dependency stub: `requirements.txt`
- Main entry imports the helper API from `plugin_kit_ai_runtime`
- Pinned runtime package version: `{{.RuntimePackageVersion}}`
{{- else }}
- Generated helper layer: `plugin/plugin_runtime.py`
- Generated dependency stub: `requirements.txt`
- Shared helper package: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on PyPI when you later want a reusable dependency instead of the vendored helper file
{{- end }}
- If `.venv` exists but is broken, `plugin-kit-ai validate --strict` will fail until you recreate it
- `plugin-kit-ai install` does not manage Python dependencies or virtualenv creation
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
- Runtime requirement: system Node.js `20+` installed on the machine running the plugin
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- Shared helper delivery: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on npm
- `package.json` already declares `plugin-kit-ai-runtime`
- Main entry imports the helper API from the shared package instead of `plugin/plugin-runtime.*`
- Pinned runtime package version: `{{.RuntimePackageVersion}}`
{{- else }}
- Generated helper layer: `plugin/plugin-runtime.{{if .TypeScript}}ts{{else}}mjs{{end}}`
- Shared helper package: `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` on npm when you later want a reusable dependency instead of the vendored helper file
{{- end }}
- Commit `package-lock.json` or an equivalent deterministic lockfile for production repos
{{- if .TypeScript }}
- Generated TypeScript scaffold: `plugin/main.ts`, `tsconfig.json`, and built output under `dist/main.js`
- `plugin-kit-ai bootstrap .` runs `npm install` and `npm run build`
{{- else }}
- Minimal JavaScript runtime scaffold using `plugin/main.mjs`
- Use `plugin-kit-ai init <name> --platform codex-runtime --runtime node --typescript` when you want the built TypeScript scaffold
{{- end }}
{{- else if eq .Runtime "shell" }}
- Runtime: POSIX shell on Unix
- On Windows, this runtime requires `bash` in `PATH`
- `plugin-kit-ai install` does not package or distribute shell runtime dependencies
{{- end }}

## First Run

{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
```bash
plugin-kit-ai doctor .
plugin-kit-ai bootstrap .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform codex-runtime --strict
plugin-kit-ai test . --platform codex-runtime --event Notify
plugin-kit-ai dev . --platform codex-runtime --event Notify
```
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
