## Stable Default

- `Notify`

Treat `plugin-kit-ai validate --strict` as the CI-grade readiness gate for this runtime lane.
Choose the Go lane instead when you want downstream users to avoid installing `{{if eq .Runtime "python"}}Python{{else if eq .Runtime "node"}}Node.js{{else}}shell dependencies{{end}}` before they can run the plugin.

## Target Files

- `plugin/launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint for local notify integration
- `plugin/targets/codex-runtime/package.yaml`: authored Codex runtime metadata
- `plugin/targets/codex-runtime/config.extra.toml`: optional passthrough for supported repo-local Codex config fields beyond managed `model` and `notify`
- `.codex/config.toml`: generated managed Codex config
- `fixtures/codex-runtime/Notify.json`: pre-generated stable Codex notify smoke payload owned by this project
- `goldens/codex-runtime/*`: pre-generated stable stdout/stderr/exit contract owned by this project
{{- if eq .Runtime "python" }}
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- `requirements.txt`: shared-helper dependency manifest for the `plugin_kit_ai_runtime` import path
{{- else }}
- `plugin/plugin_runtime.py`: official helper API for `on_notify` authoring on the Python lane
{{- end }}
{{- else if eq .Runtime "node" }}
{{- if .SharedRuntimePackage }}
- `package.json`: shared-helper dependency manifest for the `plugin-kit-ai-runtime` import path
{{- else }}
- `plugin/plugin-runtime.{{if .TypeScript}}ts{{else}}mjs{{end}}`: official helper API for `onNotify` authoring on the Node lane
{{- end }}
{{- end }}
